The authors evaluate the recall-aware scores against standard scoring metrics and find that recall-aware scores highly correlate with rule quality scores in the setting of increasingly complete KBs. 
Another line of work uses cardinality information as priors in neural link prediction [Muoz2019EmbeddingCC]. Similar to the work by Tanon et al. [pellissier2017completeness], they regularize the number of high probability predictions by penalizing the model when the number of predictions violate the cardinality bounds of a given relation type.